%N A395323 Decimal expansion of the conjecturally maximum possible volume of a polyhedron with 32 vertices inscribed in the unit sphere.
%C A395323 This polyhedron, with the symmetry group of the regular icosahedron, is based on the regular dodecahedron, in which each of the 12 pentagonal faces is replaced by an equilateral pyramid. It has 60 congruent isosceles triangles as faces. The length of its 30 longer edges is given by A381264, the length of the 60 shorter edges by A395324.
%H A395323 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A395323/b395323.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A395323 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="https://www.randomwalk.de/sphere/volmax/videos/32c.mp4">Number of edges incident with the 32 vertices</a>, video (2021).
%H A395323 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A395323 Equals 2*sqrt(50 - 10*sqrt(5))/3.
%F A395323 Equals (10/3) * A179290.
%F A395323 Equals the smallest positive root of 81*x^4 - 3600*x^2 + 32000. - _Paolo Xausa_, Apr 21 2026
%e A395323 3.5048740807942240401711272323191773819...
%t A395323 First[RealDigits[2*Sqrt[50 - 10*Sqrt[5]]/3, 10, 100]] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Apr 21 2026 *)
